# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Band Messaging – Environment Variables
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   Copy this file to .env.local for local development:
#     cp .env.local.example .env.local
#
# WHERE TO SET THESE:
#   • Local dev  →  .env.local  (this file, never commit it)
#   • Vercel     →  Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# NOTE: Convex backend functions in this project do NOT need any environment
# variables set inside the Convex dashboard. The only thing you need is the
# CONVEX_URL below, which you get FROM Convex and set HERE (in SvelteKit/Vercel).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Convex deployment URL.
# How to get it:
#   1. Run `npx convex dev`  (for local dev — URL is printed to the terminal)
#   2. Run `npx convex deploy`  (for production — URL is printed to the terminal)
#   3. Or find it in the Convex dashboard: https://dashboard.convex.dev
#      → your project → Settings → URL & Deploy Key
CONVEX_URL=

# Whether session/CSRF cookies use the Secure flag.
#   true   → always use Secure (required on Vercel / HTTPS)
#   false  → never use Secure  (use this for local HTTP dev)
#   auto   → derive from NODE_ENV (production → true, else → false)
AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE=false

# ── SET AUTOMATICALLY BY VERCEL (do not add manually) ─────────────────────────
# NODE_ENV=production
# VERCEL=1
